lyrics:
(Verse 1)
In a world where numbers dance with glee,
Aaron and Anna, just thirteen, you see.
With hearts as light as a summer breeze,
Their love blooms like flowers among the trees.

(Chorus)
Twenty-three, their magic number, sweet and true,
Aaron and Anna, forever me and you.
Hand in hand, under skies so blue,
Their love shines bright, always anew.

(Verse 2)
With every laugh, with every sigh,
Their love grows stronger, reaching high.
In their eyes, a sparkle, a joyful spree,
Aaron and Anna, a perfect harmony.

(Chorus)
Twenty-three, their magic number, sweet and true,
Aaron and Anna, forever me and you.
Hand in hand, under skies so blue,
Their love shines bright, always anew.

(Bridge)
Through ups and downs, they'll stand side by side,
